  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd -   \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "India can act as part of IMF's efforts on Sri Lanka - Former IMF Economist",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sergi Lanau, a former economist at the International Monetary Fund, currently works in the Economic Research Department of the International Monetary Fund.",
        "He has been closely observing Sri Lanka's economic situation and has been issuing warnings for a long time due to this.",
        "He comments on the weak policies employed by the rulers of Sri Lanka especially the Rajapaksas,",
        "He suggests that the government should have approached the International Monetary Fund when it realized that there were no other options to get funds.",
        "Question - Sri Lanka's foreign debt is 51 billion dollars but the country has only 25 billion in reserves that can be used to import essential goods, especially life saving drugs and fuel.",
        "Ans- The covid 19 shutdown and lack of purely principled action has left Sri Lanka in a quagmire.",
        "They paid for the bonds since they were in stock and kept the exchange rate weak and thought they would have an opportunity to access the market soon.",
        "Question- Is it ironic that the people of Sri Lanka, a tropical country rich in agricultural products, are forced to skip food, walk long distances due to lack of fuel, and expect humanitarian aid even for basic needs? What really went wrong?",
        "Ans- The country is not functioning at present, the dollar deficit is so severe that even providing essential items for survival is problematic.",
        "This is due to not making progressive changes in policies when considering Covid and not seeking help from the International Monetary Fund earlier. When the country reaches bankruptcy it is difficult to get funds even to buy essential goods.",
        "Q- We are talking about a country that plays an important role in international shipping routes, what can international financial institutions do to help Sri Lanka's economy? What conditions should be imposed by the funders as the finances have been mishandled.?",
        "International institutions can provide new dollars to Sri Lanka in exchange for a policy plan to return to sustainable growth and a debt restructuring plan. However, there must be a relatively stable government responsible for conducting negotiations and taking proposals to Parliament",
        "Q- Why do some analysts blame China and its debt trap diplomacy for this mess, how big is China's debt to Sri Lanka?",
        "Answer - We estimate that 15 percent of Sri Lanka's external debt is to China, 38 percent of bonds, and it is obvious that Sri Lanka has bought more, which means lenders have given more.",
        "For policy reforms, India can be part of the IMF's efforts to provide Sri Lanka with some dollars to find a solution to this crisis.",
        "Considering the depth of Sri Lanka's crisis, trying to find a solution for countries providing aid alone is a very difficult task."
      ],
